<TITLE> BNP govt waived Tarique firm's Tk 12 cr debt to BB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com)The past BNP-led government, straight after coming to power in 2001, wrote off a Tk 12 crore debt to Bangladesh Bank, owed by a firm of the then prime minister's son Tarique Rahman, the finance minister revealed Thursday. Just days after assuming office in October that year, the four-party alliance government waived the interest on a Tk 40.64 crore loan by the central bank to Messrs Dandy Dyeing Ltd of which Tarique, BNP chief Khaleda Zia's elder son, was a director. Finance minister AMA Muhith disclosed the information in reply to a question from Awami League MP Muhibur Rahman Manik. Muhith cited a quarterly loan report preserved in the database of the central bank's credit information bureau, showing the waiver of Tk 12,16,83,119 in interest on Oct 16, 2001. bdnew
